        <h5>Problem Statement</h5>
        <p>DfE's Skills Group Adult Education Service is responsible for tracking and tracing attendance across colleges and institutions delivering adult education throughout England. This was previously handled by a patchwork of small, single-purpose legacy applications — some pushing data via API, others relying on manual email submission to DfE. When the department decided to consolidate onto BigQuery as its single data warehouse given the scale of the data involved, those ageing on-premise applications began to fail under the demands of pushing data reliably into BigQuery. Compounding this, the rest of the DfE estate runs on Azure and SQL Server, so every interaction between that Microsoft-based estate and Google BigQuery was a recurring source of integration failures, data loss risk and operational firefighting.</p>

