        <details class="techdrop">
          <summary><svg class="icon"><use href="#i-database"/></svg>Architecture — detailed step breakdown</summary>
          <div class="techdrop-body">
            <table class="data-table">
              <tr><th>Step</th><th>Flow</th><th>Technical detail</th></tr>
              <tr><td>1</td><td>School/college MIS → Digital System</td><td>Daily automated REST/JSON API push from each institution's MIS or attendance system; manual update also available via the Cloud Run-hosted portal</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2</td><td>Digital System (PaaS)</td><td>Cloud Run hosts the portal and submission services; API Gateway publishes/secures REST endpoints for MIS integrations; Cloud Functions handle event-driven validation and notifications</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3</td><td>Digital System → Data Ingress Layer</td><td>Requests pass through the security layer (Cloud Armor, Cloud CDN) before reaching Apigee</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4</td><td>Apigee → Cloud Pub/Sub</td><td>Apigee enforces API management — throttling, quota, contract and version control — then hands off to Pub/Sub as a real-time event stream</td></tr>
              <tr><td>5</td><td>Cloud Pub/Sub → Dataflow</td><td>At-least-once delivery with ordering keys per institution; Dataflow consumes the stream, validates schema, de-duplicates and conforms records</td></tr>
              <tr><td>6</td><td>Dataflow → BigQuery</td><td>Final push loads curated records into partitioned, clustered attendance tables — the single source of truth replacing the legacy application estate</td></tr>
              <tr><td>7</td><td>BigQuery → Cloud Storage (archive)</td><td>Raw and curated data retained under lifecycle policies for audit-grade traceability and cost control</td></tr>
              <tr><td>8</td><td>BigQuery → Looker Studio / BigQuery ML</td><td>Dashboards for DfE analysts and caseworkers; ML models flag non-attendance trends and safeguarding risks</td></tr>
              <tr><td>9</td><td>BigQuery → DfE downstream systems</td><td>Funding, safeguarding and policy teams consume curated data via export or API</td></tr>
              <tr><td>10</td><td>Cross-cutting: Security Layer</td><td>Cloud KMS (CMEK), Cloud Armor (WAF/DDoS), Cloud CDN and Cloud IAM apply as a common layer across every stage — data source, digital system, ingress, warehouse and consumption</td></tr>
              <tr><td>11</td><td>Cross-cutting: Monitoring &amp; operations</td><td>Cloud Monitoring, Cloud Logging, Error Reporting and Alerting provide per-institution SLA visibility across the whole pipeline</td></tr>
            </table>
          </div>
        </details>

