  <!-- ===================== SOLUTION ARCHITECTURE (ADRs) ===================== -->
  <section class="panel" id="panel-solution">
    <div class="sheet-head"><svg class="icon sheet-icon"><use href="#i-git"/></svg><h2 class="sheet-title">Solution Architecture</h2></div>
    <p class="sheet-desc">Case studies &amp; Architecture Decision Records spanning DfE's ESFA and DDTi programmes — choreography, CQRS, orchestration, pipes &amp; filter, scatter &amp; gather, saga, and transactional outbox patterns.</p>
    <div class="dimline"></div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-001 — Choreography Pattern for Calculate Funding Service</h3><span class="adr-app">Application: CFS</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>CFS ingests high-volume datasets from multiple DfE finance sub-domains (Schools, LAs, Institutions, Funding Lines).</li>
            <li>Data arrives asynchronously via APIs, batch feeds and event streams.</li>
            <li>Funding rules must execute independently across bounded contexts.</li>
            <li>Tight coupling would create bottlenecks during peak census periods.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Adopt a fully event-driven Choreography Pattern where each microservice publishes and reacts to domain events without a central orchestrator.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Increased complexity in event versioning and schema evolution.</li>
            <li>Requires robust idempotency and replay handling.</li>
            <li>Provides a highly scalable, resilient, decoupled funding calculation engine.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Enables autonomous microservices to process funding data independently.</li>
            <li>Supports parallel execution of funding workflows.</li>
            <li>Eliminates synchronous dependencies and reduces cascading failures.</li>
            <li>Allows horizontal scaling and compensating events for eventual consistency.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/Choreography%20Pattern.png" alt="Choreography pattern diagram">
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.1 — Choreography pattern</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-002 — CQRS + Materialised Views for Funding Data Service</h3><span class="adr-app">Application: FDS, DfE ESFA</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>FDS handles millions of records from Schools, LAs and Institutions.</li>
            <li>Write workloads conflict with read workloads.</li>
            <li>Downstream systems require customised datasets and high-performance queries.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Implement CQRS with Materialised Views to separate write and read concerns.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Requires additional storage for materialised views.</li>
            <li>Eventual consistency must be communicated to consumers.</li>
            <li>Improves performance and scalability for funding analytics.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Write model optimised for ingestion and transactional consistency.</li>
            <li>Read model optimised for analytical queries and downstream reporting.</li>
            <li>Materialised views allow denormalised, indexed datasets; data sync ensures eventual consistency.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <a href="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/CQRS_Materialized%20Pattern.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/CQRS_Materialized%20Pattern.png" alt="CQRS and materialised views">
            </a>
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.2 — CQRS &amp; materialised views (click to enlarge)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-003 — Execution Orchestration Pattern for Funding Contracting Service</h3><span class="adr-app">Application: FCS, DfE ESFA</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>FCS manages dynamic workflows: contract creation, amendments, payments, validations.</li>
            <li>Workflows involve multiple independent services with different SLAs.</li>
            <li>Requires strict sequencing, retry logic and state management.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Adopt a centralised Execution Orchestration Pattern using Azure App Services, Function Apps and worker roles.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Orchestrator becomes a critical component requiring HA.</li>
            <li>Increased complexity in workflow modelling.</li>
            <li>Provides a robust, SLA-driven contracting platform.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Provides deterministic workflow sequencing and centralised error handling.</li>
            <li>Supports dynamic branching and compensating actions.</li>
            <li>Enables independent scaling of contracting sub-services and consistent lifecycle management.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <a href="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/ExecutionOrchestrationPattern.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/ExecutionOrchestrationPattern.png" alt="Execution orchestration pattern">
            </a>
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.3 — Execution orchestration pattern (click to enlarge)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-004 — Pipes &amp; Filter Pattern for DfE Connect &amp; TSI</h3><span class="adr-app">Applications: DfE Connect, TSI</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Multiple departments publish real-time data.</li>
            <li>DfE Connect must ingest, validate, enrich, and publish data to a central DB.</li>
            <li>TSI must track, trace, and correct queue-level issues.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Implement a Pipes &amp; Filter architecture with message-broker-driven filter stages.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Requires robust monitoring and DLQ management.</li>
            <li>Increased operational complexity across pipelines.</li>
            <li>Provides high throughput, resilience and modular data processing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Each filter stage runs independently with queues for back-pressure and fault isolation.</li>
            <li>TSI provides operational visibility and corrective tooling.</li>
            <li>Enables real-time, multi-threaded data processing across departments.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <a href="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/PipesFilter.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/PipesFilter.png" alt="Pipes and filter pattern">
            </a>
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.4 — Pipes &amp; Filter pattern (click to enlarge)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-005 — Scatter &amp; Gather Pattern for Data Attendance Portal</h3><span class="adr-app">Application: DDTi</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Attendance data arrives from thousands of sources.</li>
            <li>Processing must be parallelised to meet regulatory deadlines.</li>
            <li>Aggregated datasets feed downstream analytics and compliance services.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Adopt a Scatter &amp; Gather architecture using Service Bus Topics and distributed workers.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Requires careful correlation ID management.</li>
            <li>Aggregator must handle partial failures gracefully.</li>
            <li>Enables scalable, distributed attendance processing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Dispatcher scatters payloads across workers; workers process in parallel; aggregator merges results.</li>
            <li>Supports massive concurrency and high-volume ingestion.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <a href="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/Scatter_Gatter.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/Scatter_Gatter.png" alt="Scatter and gather pattern">
            </a>
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.5 — Scatter &amp; Gather pattern (click to enlarge)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-006 — Saga Pattern for CFS &amp; FCS</h3><span class="adr-app">Applications: CFS, FCS</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Funding lifecycle spans multiple services: calculation → contracting → release.</li>
            <li>Requires distributed transaction management without 2PC.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Implement a hybrid Saga architecture combining orchestration + choreography.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Requires careful modelling of compensating transactions.</li>
            <li>Eventual consistency must be accepted by stakeholders.</li>
            <li>Provides a resilient, distributed funding lifecycle engine.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Local transactions per service ensure autonomy; compensating actions provide rollback safety.</li>
            <li>Outbox + idempotency ensures reliable event publishing.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <a href="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/dfe_esfa_saga_architecture.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/dfe_esfa_saga_architecture.png" alt="Saga architecture">
            </a>
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.6 — Saga architecture (click to enlarge)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="adr">
      <div class="adr-head"><h3>ADR-007 — Transactional Outbox Pattern for Digital Forms &amp; Adults Attendance</h3><span class="adr-app">Applications: Digital Forms (ESFA), Adults Attendance Portal (DDTi)</span></div>
      <div class="adr-body">
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Context</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Both applications require reliable event publishing and downstream dataset generation.</li>
            <li>Dual-write inconsistencies previously caused data loss and audit failures.</li>
          </ul>
          <h6>Decision</h6>
          <div class="decision">Implement the Transactional Outbox Pattern with sequenced event dispatch.</div>
          <h6>Consequences</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Requires additional storage and polling infrastructure.</li>
            <li>Slight delay introduced due to asynchronous dispatch.</li>
            <li>Provides guaranteed delivery, ordering and auditability.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="adr-col">
          <h6>Rationale</h6>
          <ul>
            <li>Ensures atomic writes between main table and outbox; SequenceID guarantees ordering.</li>
            <li>Enables exactly-once processing and audit-grade traceability.</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="adr-img">
            <img src="https://priyaanka.blob.core.windows.net/arinportfolio/TransactionalOutBox.png" alt="Transactional outbox pattern">
            <div class="cap">Fig. A4.7 — Transactional Outbox pattern</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

